{
  "text": "A joint treatment of color and shape has been proposed by Fang et al. [CITATION_1] . The authors compute a feature map of the entire image frame, based on color and gradient information, while incorporating a geometry model of signs. Still, their approach requires a manual threshold tuning, and it is reported to be computationally rather expensive.",
